@subsubsection Text-form-control

@b{Description}

This represents a INPUT TYPE=TEXT or TEXTAREA form control tag.

@noindent @b{Optional-input-slots}

@b{:cols}

@itemize {}

 @item Integer. The number of columns for a TEXTAREA (if rows is > 1). Defaults to (the size).

@end itemize

@b{:password?}

@itemize {}

 @item Boolean. Specifies whether this should be a password form control with obscured screen text. 
Note that this does not automatically give encrypted transmission to the server - you need SSL
for that. Defaults to nil. Use password-form-control to get a default of t.

@end itemize

@b{:rows}

@itemize {}

 @item Integer. The number of rows. If more than 1, this will be a TEXTAREA. Defaults to 1.

@end itemize





